  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4943",
  "title": "chore: disallow direct `window` access",
  "body": "This PR disallows direct access to the `window` object to keep the library SSR-friendly.\r\n\r\n## ESLint rule\r\n\r\nThe `no-restricted-globals` ESLint rule was added to our source files (except our tests and widgets which are running on browser environments). It errors when you access directly `window`:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6137112/138685248-a5e7fa3e-a98f-4d6d-a3c3-562aeeb64a26.png)\r\n\r\n## Safely running code on the browser\r\n\r\nThere's now an internal helper to help us run code safely on browsers:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nsafelyRunOnBrowser(({ window }) => {\r\n  // Safely access `window`\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Safely running code on the server\r\n\r\nThe `fallback` option is used to run code on the server:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst location = safelyRunOnBrowser(({ window }) => window.location, {\r\n  fallback: () => {\r\n    throw new Error(\r\n      'You need to provide `getLocation` to the `history` router in environments where `window` does not exist.'\r\n    );\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that `safelyRunOnBrowser` returns the value of the callback, which is handy to use as an expression.",
